AIM:
Write a simple application, create a Docker image, containerize it, push it to Docker Hub, and remove the image using Docker.

--------------------------------------------------
index.html
--------------------------------------------------

<h1>Hello Docker</h1>

--------------------------------------------------
Dockerfile
--------------------------------------------------

FROM nginx:latest
COPY index.html /usr/share/nginx/html/index.html

--------------------------------------------------
Build Image
--------------------------------------------------

docker build -t myapp .

--------------------------------------------------
Run Container
--------------------------------------------------

docker run -d -p 8080:80 --name mycontainer myapp

--------------------------------------------------
Login to Docker Hub
--------------------------------------------------

docker login

--------------------------------------------------
Tag Image
--------------------------------------------------

docker tag myapp YOUR_DOCKERHUB_USERNAME/myapp:v1

--------------------------------------------------
Push Image to Docker Hub
--------------------------------------------------

docker push YOUR_DOCKERHUB_USERNAME/myapp:v1

--------------------------------------------------
Stop and Remove Container
--------------------------------------------------

docker stop mycontainer
docker rm mycontainer

--------------------------------------------------
Remove Images
--------------------------------------------------

docker rmi myapp
docker rmi YOUR_DOCKERHUB_USERNAME/myapp:v1

--------------------------------------------------
RESULT
--------------------------------------------------

Successfully created a Docker image, containerized the application, pushed the image to Docker Hub, and removed the Docker images.
